h5.summary

As per the documentation (see [Transitioning an Issue|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AGILE/Transitioning+an+Issue]), when Issues are dragged between columns, available statuses should be displayed:
{quote}If the target column is associated with more than one status then, when the issue is hovered over that column, each status will appear as a separate section with a dashed outline{quote}

However, it's the transition names that are displayed; for transitions that weren't included in the original Simplified Workflow.

h5.steps to reproduce
# create a Project and a board for it;
# associate more than one status to one of the columns;
# attempt to drag an Issue into the column containing more than one status - the transition name will be displayed instead of the Status name.

*Additional notes:*
- this doesn't affect default transitions in the Simplified Workflow, as they have the _jira.i18n.title_ property set to _gh.workflow.preset.\[value\]_;
- new statuses and transitions added using Agile (from *Board > Configure > Column*) don't have that property, and are displayed incorrectly.

